a serial killer?

1153
01:00:51,229 --> 01:00:52,889
That's an expensive present.

1154
01:00:54,030 --> 01:00:57,393
The Lymans are so wealthy.
Yes.

1155
01:00:57,462 --> 01:00:59,223
It was almost
too extravagant.

1156
01:00:59,629 --> 01:01:02,789
I'd better get ready.
I still haven't found
my millionaire yet.

1157
01:01:04,062 --> 01:01:05,050
(SIGHS)

1158
01:01:06,162 --> 01:01:08,628
Oh, God, Sondra, what a mess!

1159
01:01:10,829 --> 01:01:12,158
It's starting to add up
against him.

1160
01:01:12,229 --> 01:01:13,991
Bits and scraps
are coming together.

1161
01:01:14,062 --> 01:01:15,460
God, it's you!

1162
01:01:15,663 --> 01:01:18,254
I sensed
you were falling in love.
I escaped again.

1163
01:01:18,362 --> 01:01:21,988
It's just circumstantial junk,
you know. A coincidence
here and there.

1164
01:01:22,062 --> 01:01:24,085
Too much smoke
not to be fire.

1165
01:01:24,196 --> 01:01:26,526
Look, I'm sure
you've been wrong
plenty of times.

1166
01:01:26,596 --> 01:01:27,755
Not wrong here.

1167
01:01:27,829 --> 01:01:31,283
Though I agree
you haven't got enough
to pull the trigger yet.

1168
01:01:31,462 --> 01:01:33,690
If you act prematurely,
not only does he walk,

1169
01:01:33,763 --> 01:01:36,854
your professional credibility
is wrecked,
sometimes for good.

1170
01:01:36,930 --> 01:01:38,862
Oh, I'm sure you want him
to be guilty.

1171
01:01:38,963 --> 01:01:40,986
You know, that way you get
your last big scoop.

1172
01:01:41,095 --> 01:01:42,493
I'm beginning to fade.

1173
01:01:42,563 --> 01:01:44,392
Sondra, don't let me down!

1174
01:01:44,462 --> 01:01:46,553
I wish you'd fade for good!

1175
01:01:46,729 --> 01:01:47,888
Get out of my life!

1176
01:01:47,963 --> 01:01:49,394
I'm not
cut out for this.

1177
01:01:49,462 --> 01:01:51,985
I should be
flossing molars for a living.

1178
01:01:53,029 --> 01:01:55,723
The bread is... You know,
I can make a meal
just with the bread.

1179
01:01:55,796 --> 01:01:57,694
I can do a whole meal,
just nothing but bread.

1180
01:01:57,896 --> 01:02:00,726
If I ate that much bread,
I'd be 20 pounds heavier.

1181
01:02:00,796 --> 01:02:02,659
See,
I never gain an ounce,

1182
01:02:02,729 --> 01:02:06,855
because, you know,
my anxiety acts like aerobics.

1183
01:02:07,129 --> 01:02:08,527
So I get the exercise.

1184
01:02:09,362 --> 01:02:12,055
Thanks for taking me out
for my birthday, Sidney.

1185
01:02:12,162 --> 01:02:14,651
Well, you know,
you're the daughter
that I never had.

1186
01:02:14,729 --> 01:02:16,718
Oh, that's so...
No, no, I'm kidding.
I'm kidding.

1187
01:02:16,796 --> 01:02:18,193
'Cause I never wanted
to have kids.

1188
01:02:18,596 --> 01:02:20,892
I didn't.
Because you have kids,
what is it?

1189
01:02:21,196 --> 01:02:23,991
You know, you're nice
to them, you bring
them up, you suffer,

1190
01:02:24,062 --> 01:02:25,551
you take care of them

1191
01:02:25,629 --> 01:02:30,061
and then they grow up
and they accuse you
of having Alzheimer's.

1192
01:02:30,596 --> 01:02:32,186
Could you
ever live in London?

1193
01:02:33,763 --> 01:02:35,228
Could I live
in London? No.

1194
01:02:35,296 --> 01:02:37,489
And I love London.
Don't get me wrong,
I love London,

1195
01:02:37,563 --> 01:02:39,756
but, you know,

1196
01:02:40,062 --> 01:02:43,790
apart from
the language problem,
I can't take the driving.

1197
01:02:43,863 --> 01:02:46,920
Because it, you know,
it's on the wrong side,
and I...

1198
01:02:47,362 --> 01:02:49,157
Every time
I drive a car here,

1199
01:02:49,229 --> 01:02:51,491
I'm convinced
I'm going to die in a crash.

1200
01:02:52,829 --> 01:02:53,817
Sidney!

1201
01:02:53,995 --> 01:02:54,983
What's the matter?

1202
01:02:55,629 --> 01:02:56,924
It's Peter.

1203
01:02:56,995 --> 01:02:58,052
You said
Peter was out of town.

1204
01:02:58,129 --> 01:02:59,958
Well, that's
what he told me.

1205
01:03:00,529 --> 01:03:01,517
Come on.

1206
01:03:01,696 --> 01:03:02,956
What do you mean, come on?

1207
01:03:03,029 --> 01:03:05,188
(STUTTERING)
I ordered prawns.

1208
01:03:05,396 --> 01:03:07,487
Just pay, all right?
Just pay.

1209
01:03:07,763 --> 01:03:09,854
What do you mean, pay?
All I do is...

1210
01:03:09,929 --> 01:03:12,020
Fine, it's her birthday.

1211
01:03:15,296 --> 01:03:16,353
Come on.

1212
01:03:16,763 --> 01:03:18,888
Maybe he's got
another woman on the side,

1213
01:03:18,995 --> 01:03:21,961
and he likes you,
but he's sexually
attracted to her.

1214
01:03:22,262 --> 01:03:23,421
Thanks, Sidney.

1215
01:03:23,496 --> 01:03:25,121
Well, why doesn't he have
his chauffeur?

1216
01:03:25,196 --> 01:03:27,162
I don't know,
whatever he's doing,
he must want it to be secret.

1217
01:04:04,095 --> 01:04:06,425
Oh, I told you
he went the other way!

1218
01:04:06,895 --> 01:04:08,486
Can we go home, please?

1219
01:04:08,563 --> 01:04:10,324
It's starting to rain.

1220
01:04:10,396 --> 01:04:12,794
(GROANS) I can't believe
he lied to me.

1221
01:04:13,029 --> 01:04:16,689
Maybe he's doing
something that he's ashamed
to tell you about.

1222
01:04:16,763 --> 01:04:20,627
Maybe he belongs to
one of those clubs, or he's
a cross-dresser or something.

1223
01:04:20,696 --> 01:04:22,854
Or maybe
he does folk dancing.

1224
01:04:22,962 --> 01:04:25,394
Oh, I'm sure
it's probably something
that when he tells me,

1225
01:04:25,462 --> 01:04:27,485
I'll just feel foolish
for thinking he lied.

1226
01:04:27,563 --> 01:04:30,791
I'm sure. You know,
not everything in
this world is sinister.

1227
01:04:30,862 --> 01:04:32,624
You know,
just practically everything.

1228
01:04:32,696 --> 01:04:35,526
(GROANS) That Indian food
made me sick.

1229
01:04:36,095 --> 01:04:39,084
You hardly touched
your cobra salad.
How can you be sick?

1230
01:04:39,362 --> 01:04:41,123
WOMAN: (SCREAMING) Help!

1231
01:04:41,196 --> 01:04:43,855
A woman's been strangled!

1232
01:04:44,362 --> 01:04:48,761
Help!
A woman's been strangled!
Help, call the police!

1233
01:04:48,828 --> 01:04:50,817
MAN: Somebody call the police!
There's been a murder!

1234
01:04:50,895 --> 01:04:52,191
WOMAN 2: There's been
a murder upstairs.

1235
01:04:52,262 --> 01:04:53,250
WOMAN 1: Help!

1236
01:04:53,362 --> 01:04:55,351
MAN: Have you got a phone?
Have you got a phone?
Call the police.

1237
01:04:55,429 --> 01:04:58,224
Could it be the Tarot Killer?
They found a Tarot card.
It's him.

1238
01:04:58,296 --> 01:04:59,694
I can't believe it!
She lives in this building.

1239
01:04:59,763 --> 01:05:01,921
It's him again.
They found the Tarot card.

1240
01:05:03,563 --> 01:05:06,393
Elizabeth Gibson,
another short-haired brunette.

1241
01:05:06,629 --> 01:05:09,186
(SIGHS) We should have
gone to the police earlier.

1242
01:05:09,296 --> 01:05:12,319
Well, you know...
You said that they
wouldn't believe us

1243
01:05:12,396 --> 01:05:14,589
and they may not.

1244
01:05:14,962 --> 01:05:18,417
Sidney, it's about time
we show my story to
a real newspaperman.

1245
01:05:19,563 --> 01:05:20,892
By real, you mean what?

1246
01:05:21,062 --> 01:05:22,153
One that's living.

1247
01:05:22,596 --> 01:05:25,357
Vivian's father has a friend
that works at The Observer.

1248
01:05:27,029 --> 01:05:29,325
Well, it's very vivid
and rather shocking,

1249
01:05:29,396 --> 01:05:32,226
and there are some
genuine circumstantial
bits of evidence.

1250
01:05:32,296 --> 01:05:36,023
But let me give you a lesson
in professional journalism.

1251
01:05:37,229 --> 01:05:40,820
No newspaper should
or would ever run this story.

1252
01:05:41,563 --> 01:05:43,051
What? Why?

1253
01:05:43,696 --> 01:05:46,820
It would be
fatally irresponsible
and libelous.

1254
01:05:47,496 --> 01:05:50,428
All you have here
are a number
of titillating speculations.

1255
01:05:51,296 --> 01:05:54,989
Flamboyant theories that
tarnish a man, and a
well-known figure at that,

1256
01:05:55,062 --> 01:05:57,620
without a single shred
of substantial proof.

1257
01:05:58,762 --> 01:06:00,921
So his mother
was a short-haired brunette.

1258
01:06:01,062 --> 01:06:02,891
So he came late
for a poker game

1259
01:06:02,962 --> 01:06:06,520
and said he was going away
on a business trip
and he got caught lying.

1260
01:06:06,828 --> 01:06:11,591
Yes, but who keeps
a Tarot deck under
a French horn?

1261
01:06:12,396 --> 01:06:16,419
It's not against the law
to own a Tarot deck,
or keep it wherever you like.

1262
01:06:17,862 --> 01:06:20,158
You'd look
pretty foolish in court
with your accusations,

1263
01:06:20,229 --> 01:06:21,854
and that's
where you'll wind up.

1264
01:06:22,229 --> 01:06:25,218
Because he'd have no choice
but to sue you
and the newspaper,

1265
01:06:25,296 --> 01:06:26,421
and he'd win.

1266
01:06:26,862 --> 01:06:28,226
And to go to the police?

1267
01:06:29,062 --> 01:06:30,255
I'll come to that.

1268
01:06:30,329 --> 01:06:33,489
But first let me
continue my tedious
professorial lecture.

1269
01:06:35,262 --> 01:06:37,387
Vivian's dad and I
go way back.

1270
01:06:37,795 --> 01:06:39,886
He said you were
a journalism student.

1271
01:06:40,663 --> 01:06:41,651
Hmm.

1272
01:06:42,696 --> 01:06:44,286
You talk about getting a tip.

1273
01:06:44,496 --> 01:06:46,325
Okay, you won't
disclose your source,

1274
01:06:46,396 --> 01:06:49,521
but what you have done
is let your imagination
run wild.

1275
01:06:49,663 --> 01:06:50,719
No, no.

1276
01:06:50,795 --> 01:06:54,353
What if I told you
that my source happened
to be a certain Joe Strombel?

1277
01:06:54,995 --> 01:06:56,893
The late Joe Strombel?
Yep.

1278
01:06:56,962 --> 01:06:59,394
You mean, before he died
he gave a student reporter

1279
01:06:59,462 --> 01:07:01,791
a major story
and didn't follow
it up himself?

1280
01:07:01,862 --> 01:07:04,556
We didn't say
it was before he died.

1281
01:07:05,695 --> 01:07:07,059
What?
No, it...

1282
01:07:07,129 --> 01:07:08,685
He got the story
before he died,

1283
01:07:08,762 --> 01:07:11,194
and then he died
before he could follow it up.

1284
01:07:12,929 --> 01:07:16,191
(CHUCKLES) Well,
why did he give it to you?
He didn't know he was dying.

1285
01:07:16,496 --> 01:07:17,655
I don't buy it.

1286
01:07:17,728 --> 01:07:19,285
I knew Joe Strombel well.

1287
01:07:19,629 --> 01:07:21,958
If he'd had a tip
that he considered reliable,

1288
01:07:22,596 --> 01:07:24,619
he would certainly
have pursued it himself,

1289
01:07:24,695 --> 01:07:26,594
from the grave,
if necessary.

1290
01:07:27,795 --> 01:07:30,591
What about how Peter
was in the neighborhood

1291
01:07:30,662 --> 01:07:32,685
the night
the murder was committed?

1292
01:07:32,795 --> 01:07:33,783
(CLEARS THROAT)

1293
01:07:33,895 --> 01:07:36,259
I realize as a student
how exciting it must have been

1294
01:07:36,329 --> 01:07:38,954
to think that you were onto
something so spectacular.

1295
01:07:39,095 --> 01:07:40,561
Hey, she is onto something!

1296
01:07:40,629 --> 01:07:42,685
This kid is a bloodhound.
Look at her!

1297
01:07:42,762 --> 01:07:46,286
She could sell the story
to any tabloid in town.

1298
01:07:46,929 --> 01:07:47,917
Hmm.

1299
01:07:48,862 --> 01:07:51,987
Now that I've preached
on the realities
of accurate reporting,

1300
01:07:52,062 --> 01:07:56,085
I want to tell you
how catastrophic
for everybody involved

1301
01:07:56,162 --> 01:07:58,287
it would have been
if you had, say, taken

1302
01:07:58,362 --> 01:08:01,487
the results
of your investigation
to a tabloid.

1303
01:08:02,828 --> 01:08:06,386
Today, the police
have apprehended
the Tarot Card Serial Killer.

1304
01:08:06,995 --> 01:08:09,756
And it most assuredly
is not Peter Lyman.

1305
01:08:10,262 --> 01:08:11,489
What?

1306
01:08:11,563 --> 01:08:14,653
Every paper in town
is going to press
with it as we speak.

1307
01:08:15,529 --> 01:08:19,256
It was a handyman
named Henry Banks
who has confessed.

1308
01:08:19,962 --> 01:08:23,122
Banks is a delusional paranoid
who's given Scotland Yard

1309
01:08:23,196 --> 01:08:25,855
information
that only the killer
could possibly know.

1310
01:08:26,695 --> 01:08:28,491
He's led the police
to two additional bodies

1311
01:08:28,563 --> 01:08:32,393
and his DNA
and a fingerprint
they found check out.

1312
01:08:33,496 --> 01:08:35,723
I know
this puts a crimp
in your scoop,

1313
01:08:36,563 --> 01:08:39,324
but Henry Banks is
the Tarot Card Serial Killer.

1314
01:08:40,229 --> 01:08:41,717
Not Lord Lyman's son.

1315
01:08:44,429 --> 01:08:46,224
Well, I can't say
I'm not walking on air.

1316
01:08:47,129 --> 01:08:50,323
Oh, Jesus, If I ever catch
that Joe Strombel,
I'll kill him.

1317
01:08:50,396 --> 01:08:52,385
I only hope
Peter forgives me
for what I've done.

1318
01:08:52,462 --> 01:08:53,553
For what?

1319
01:08:53,628 --> 01:08:55,561
I lied to him.
I'm not Jade Spence.

1320
01:08:55,628 --> 01:08:59,061
I'm a pushy,
duplicitous, ambitious
college student.

1321
01:08:59,129 --> 01:09:00,117
I lied to him,
over and over.

1322
01:09:00,229 --> 01:09:02,558
Darling, he lied to you, too,
so it's even.

1323
01:09:02,628 --> 01:09:06,026
His lies pale in comparison
to the enormity
of what I've done.

1324
01:09:06,529 --> 01:09:09,585
So marry him
as Jade Spence.
Don't tell him.

1325
01:09:09,662 --> 01:09:12,992
(STUTTERING) You know,
you don't have to be
Sondra Pransky ever again.

1326
01:09:13,062 --> 01:09:14,494
Marry him as Jade Spence.

1327
01:09:14,562 --> 01:09:17,585
Yeah, but I don't want to
have to get you a
Father's Day gift every year.

1328
01:09:17,929 --> 01:09:22,554
You know, I don't know how to
break this to you, honey,
but you were adopted. Okay?

1329
01:09:22,628 --> 01:09:24,560
Your mother and I,
we were at the orphanage,

1330
01:09:24,628 --> 01:09:26,924
we wanted
a handicapped child, and...

1331
01:09:27,662 --> 01:09:30,322
Ah, finally.
Just you and I all weekend.

1332
01:09:30,462 --> 01:09:31,450
Yeah.

1333
01:09:33,362 --> 01:09:34,918
I thought you'd like it here.

1334
01:09:35,129 --> 01:09:36,459
It's lovely.
Mmm-hmm.

1335
01:09:39,062 --> 01:09:40,721
Peter?
Yes.

1336
01:09:40,795 --> 01:09:43,318
I have
a confession to make.
Oh, God, so do I.

1337
01:09:43,828 --> 01:09:45,817
Oh, well, let me go first.

1338
01:09:45,895 --> 01:09:47,793
Actually, no,
let me, please,

1339
01:09:47,862 --> 01:09:49,158
because mine's
been bothering me all day.

1340
01:09:49,262 --> 01:09:50,591
I just want
to get it off my chest.

1341
01:09:50,662 --> 01:09:54,425
When I told you I was
going away for a few days
on business,

1342
01:09:54,562 --> 01:09:56,892
I was lying.

1343
01:09:57,728 --> 01:09:59,717
I know.
You know? How?

1344
01:10:00,396 --> 01:10:02,453
Oh, I saw you.
You saw me? No.

1345
01:10:02,795 --> 01:10:05,193
I was at dinner, and...
With your father?

1346
01:10:05,628 --> 01:10:08,822
Actually...
Well, anyway,
it doesn't matter. Really.

1347
01:10:09,196 --> 01:10:13,094
The truth is,
that a company my father owns

1348
01:10:13,162 --> 01:10:14,821
is about to merge
with a company
in the Middle East.

1349
01:10:14,895 --> 01:10:16,861
It's a very
sensitive situation,

1350
01:10:16,929 --> 01:10:18,622
and the less
anyone knows about it,
the better.

1351
01:10:18,695 --> 01:10:20,286
And we just didn't want
the press to sniff it out.

1352
01:10:20,362 --> 01:10:21,554
I mean,
that's no excuse, really.

1353
01:10:21,628 --> 01:10:23,958
I'm just very sorry
for the extreme secrecy.

1354
01:10:24,029 --> 01:10:27,086
No, no, no, it's fine.
I'm glad.

1355
01:10:27,162 --> 01:10:30,889
It's your own
secret information.
That's fine.

1356
01:10:30,962 --> 01:10:33,224
So your father took you out
for a birthday dinner

1357
01:10:33,296 --> 01:10:34,989
and you saw me.
I mean, how unnerving.

1358
01:10:35,062 --> 01:10:37,892
God, I mean, the thing
I hate most in the world
is lying.

1359
01:10:39,029 --> 01:10:40,154
Uh-huh.

1360
01:10:40,795 --> 01:10:41,852
What?

1361
01:10:43,562 --> 01:10:44,926
Peter...
Yes, Jade?

1362
01:10:46,495 --> 01:10:47,483
Peter...

1363
01:10:47,562 --> 01:10:49,653
Oh, yes.
What did you want to tell me?

1364
01:10:49,795 --> 01:10:50,818
Uh...

1365
01:10:50,895 --> 01:10:52,656
Jade, there's nothing
you can tell me that...

1366
01:10:52,728 --> 01:10:55,024
My name is not Jade Spence.

1367
01:10:56,062 --> 01:10:57,392
It's not?

1368
01:10:58,329 --> 01:11:00,420
No. It's Sondra Pransky.

1369
01:11:01,029 --> 01:11:04,654
And my father
is not my father.
His name is Sidney Waterman.

1370
01:11:04,728 --> 01:11:06,626
He's a magician
called Splendini.

1371
01:11:06,695 --> 01:11:08,218
I'm a journalism student.

1372
01:11:08,795 --> 01:11:12,989
Don't ask me
what kind of crazy
misinformation we received

1373
01:11:13,062 --> 01:11:14,994
to believe you might be
the Tarot Card Killer.

1374
01:11:15,062 --> 01:11:19,222
(STUTTERING) I mean,
I didn't know you
at this time. Remember?

1375
01:11:19,695 --> 01:11:22,525
And, of course,
as soon as I got to know you,

1376
01:11:22,595 --> 01:11:24,925
I knew that
it couldn't possibly be true.

1377
01:11:24,995 --> 01:11:27,120
And the police have him now,
so everything's fine.

1378
01:11:27,628 --> 01:11:30,026
Of course,
along the route
I fell for you,

1379
01:11:30,095 --> 01:11:32,720
and now
I totally blew it, and...

